        <type>bool</type>
        <definition>DALI_ADAPTOR_API bool Dali::DevelApplication::AddIdleWithReturnValue</definition>
        <argsstring>(Application application, CallbackBase *callback)</argsstring>
        <name>AddIdleWithReturnValue</name>
        <qualifiedname>Dali::DevelApplication::AddIdleWithReturnValue</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="classDali_1_1Application" kindref="compound">Application</ref></type>
          <declname>application</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>CallbackBase *</type>
          <declname>callback</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Ensures that the function passed in is called from the main loop when it is idle. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">application</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A handle to the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Application" kindref="compound">Application</ref> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">callback</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The function to call </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><computeroutput>true</computeroutput> if added successfully, <computeroutput>false</computeroutput> otherwise</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Function must be called from main event thread only</para>
</simplesect>
A callback of the following type should be used: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keywordtype">bool</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>MyFunction();</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> This callback will be called repeatedly as long as it returns true. A return of 0 deletes this callback.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Ownership of the callback is passed onto this class. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
